{"handle": "tooling", "community_addon": {"id": "kp910a", "enabled": true, "addon_id": "wiki", "parameters": "{\\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Tools Community Calls\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"subtitle\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\" The community calls are informal sessions where we share updates, discuss tooling and present projects in the NEAR ecosystem.\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThese sessions are now at a regular interval taking place **Every Second Tuesday of the month** if you dont want to miss those make sure you follow **[DevHub Community Calendar](https://calendar.google.com/calendar/u/2/r?cid=c_f54ed37fd92327acdc7e4343fe40722ae5797b6c82929ba93e9f3a89c69657ab@group.calendar.google.com&pli=1)**. \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIf you want to present your work, suggest discussion topics or simply get in touch - **[Join our Telegram group](https://t.me/NEAR_Tools_Community_Group)**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n---------\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nHere are the recaps of our most recent community calls:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n---------\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n### **[Community Call] #6: May 14, 2024**\\\\\\\\n[![Tools Community Call #6](https://i.imgur.com/LHXt3u6.png)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bfCFOwGZCDo)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Watch on YouTube: [Tools Community Call #6 \\\\u{2013} near/dev/hub](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bfCFOwGZCDo)**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Recap:**\\\\\\\\n- **Zahid** Gives updates on Jutsu.ai and talks about Bento \\\\\\\\n  * Q&A with Zahid\\\\\\\\n- **Jacob** presents NEAR Contract Tools\\\\\\\\n  * Q&A with Jacob\\\\\\\\n  * differences between NEAR Contract Tools and NEAR Contract Tools, \\\\\\\\n  * possibilities for cargo near extensions and collaborations\\\\\\\\n- **Vlad** presents ecosystem updates\\\\\\\\n  * near.cli.rs\\\\\\\\n  * near-jsonrpc-client-rs\\\\\\\\n  * near-api-js \\\\\\\\n  * upcomming rust sdk 5.2.0 that brings IterableMap & IterableSet \\\\\\\\n  * mentions the works of reproducible builds \\\\\\\\n  * presents collaboration opportunities on JS and Rust SDKs \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Links from chat:**\\\\\\\\nhttps://bento.jutsu.ai/\\\\\\\\nhttps://github.com/near/near-sdk-contract-tools\\\\\\\\nhttps://near.org/contractwizard.near/widget/ContractWizardUI\\\\\\\\nhttps://github.com/near/contract-wizard\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n----------\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n### **[Community Call] #5: Apr 9, 2024**\\\\\\\\n[![Tools Community Call #5](https://ipfs.near.social/ipfs/bafkreigo3mpikbg2ogjipjonelfbvnrtypx6hkyr3rszaicyi3pgxhwyou)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EDCoWObguVs)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Watch on YouTube: [Tools Community Call #5 \\\\u{2013} near/dev/hub](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EDCoWObguVs)**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Recap:**\\\\\\\\n- **Vlad** Presents the updates of Rust SDK - v5.1 That reduces the boiler plate necessary for writing smart contracts.\\\\\\\\n Next version coming soon will bring \\\\u{201c}iterable map\\\\u{201d}.\\\\\\\\n- **LedgerApp** rewrite in Rust is complete and going through a formal security audit. Expecting to go live in May\\\\\\\\n- **[Cargo Near](https://github.com/near/cargo-near)** and **rust-sdk** are getting integrated with **SourceScan** making the contracts source code verifiable and discoverable\\\\\\\\n checkout the [NEP-330 here](https://github.com/near/NEPs/pull/533)\\\\\\\\n- **Morgan** presents **Okashi.dev** rewrite he did for ETH Denver simulating Near environment for interacting with smart contracts in the browser locally :blown:\\\\\\\\n- **Re:Public** showcase their entry for ETH London and present [their roadmap and proposal](https://near.social/devhub.near/widget/app?page=proposal&id=33)\\\\\\\\n- **[bos-workspace](https://github.com/NEARBuilders/bos-workspace)** had a rewrite making it more modular and easier to be worked with presented by **Elliot**\\\\\\\\n- **Yuval** - tight for record holder attendee of the community calls recaps Q1 and great stats of **LavaNet.xyz** speaks about what\\\\\\'s next\\\\\\\\n- **Zahid** Recaps [Q1 updates](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LuwX8InOQdU&ab_channel=JutsuAI) and [milestones](https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/jutsu-devhub-collaboration-q1-milestones-tryjutsu-zacec/?trackingId=pgauiK2OUj2s782z5cIhfw%3D%3D). Shares the [roadmap](https://trello.com/b/NUIKq7dq/jutsu-public-roadmap) for **Jutsu.ai**\\\\\\\\n- **NearBlocks** represented by **Luke** Shares some stats and recent updates supporting our ecosystem.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n----------\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n### **[Community Call] #4: Wed Mar 6, 2024**\\\\\\\\n[![Tools Community Call #4](https://i.imgur.com/eR30Vrg.jpeg)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Rd3Vn09c-Goi)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Watch on YouTube: [Tools Community Group Call #4 \\\\u{2013} near/dev/hub](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kcKigCtsHDo)**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Recap:**\\\\\\\\n**Zahid** demoes copilot and generative UI feature built in** Jutsu.ai**.\\\\\\\\n**Yuval** overviews **LavaNet.xyz **and introduces Lava Points, provides stats of current usage.\\\\\\\\n**Euguene** introduces **FastNear.com** and talks about the infrastructure problems it aiming to solve.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n----------\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n### **[Community Call] #3: Feb 21, 2024**\\\\\\\\n[![Tools Community Call #3](https://i.imgur.com/UdPKO4F.jpeg)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kcKigCtsHDo&list=PLrLLmjcJVAB9RoK95udIqkVE_JqHt_CCd)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Watch on YouTube [Tools Community Group Call #3 \\\\u{2013} near/dev/hub](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kcKigCtsHDo&list=PLrLLmjcJVAB9RoK95udIqkVE_JqHt_CCd)**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Recap:**\\\\\\\\n- **Oleg Kuzmin** discusses the new implementation of **LedgerApp**.\\\\\\\\n- **Ricardo** presents his team and **AgorApp** https://agorapp.dev.\\\\\\\\n- **Guillermo** shares about recently updated **near-cli** https://github.com/near/near-cli.\\\\\\\\n- **Jaswinder** from Harmonic Guild presents their current work on **near-api-rs** https://github.com/Harmonic-Guild/nea...\\\\\\\\n- **S\\\\u{e9}rgio Seco** introduces **near-relay** https://github.com/SurgeCode/near-relay.\\\\\\\\n- **Frol** talks about **NEAR\\\\\\'s Rust Stack**.\\\\\\\\n- **Zahid** from **Jutsu.ai** gives a last-minute heads-up that breaking changes have been introduced, with more to be announced and discussed on the next community call.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n---------\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**All sessions can be found on the [DevHub YouTube Channel](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vg9LYGLU7ok&list=PLrLLmjcJVAB9RoK95udIqkVE_JqHt_CCd)**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n---------\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"textAlign\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"left\\\\\\\"}", "display_name": "Community Calls"}}

{"data": {"post": {"main": "{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"md\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"**Hello Protocol Community** \\\\u{1f3c6}\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWe\\\\\\'re excited to announce our upcoming release, version 1.40 of the protocol, which will soon be deployed to TestNet. \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis release introduces an essential feature called Yield/Resume, detailed in [NEP-519](https://github.com/near/NEPs/pull/519). \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis feature empowers contract developers by enabling them to establish function dependencies, particularly external data dependencies. In simpler terms, it allows smart contract developers to defer response calls, enhancing flexibility and efficiency in their applications.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nStay tuned for further updates and let us know if you have any questions or feedback.\\\\\\\"}"}, "index": {"post": "{\\\\\\\"key\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"main\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"value\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"md\\\\\\\"}}"}}, "handle": "protocol"}

In simpler terms, it allows smart contract developers to defer response calls, enhancing flexibility and efficiency in their applications.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nStay tuned for further updates and let us know if you have any questions or feedback.\\\\\\\"}"}, "index": {"post": "{\\\\\\\"key\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"main\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"value\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"md\\\\\\\"}}"}}}}

{"id": 81, "body": {"name": "`store` collections integration tests.", "summary": "The goal of this proposal is to cover the `store` collections with integration tests demonstrating their GAS usage. This should also allow for spotting performance degradation should any underlying code be updated.", "category": "Tooling & Infrastructure", "timeline": {"status": "DRAFT"}, "supervisor": "frol.near", "description": "# Overview \\\\nThe goal of this proposal is to cover the `store` collections with integration tests demonstrating their GAS usage. This should also allow for spotting performance degradation should any underlying code be updated.\\\\n\\\\n# Background\\\\n`store::Iterable*` collections replaced `store::Unordered*` and we need to verify that the average performance is indeed better, especially considering `store::Unordered*` bottlenecks related to removals.\\\\n\\\\n# Deliverables\\\\n1. Covering `store` collections with integration tests based on [workspace-rs examples](https://github.com/shariffdev/workspaces-rs/blob/e500c6049f273ce473a85557815a6f6c4dcfa145/workspaces/tests/gas_meter.rs), fixing the amount of operations to consume `100TGas`. This will allow us to spot if any of the code changes to those or underlying collections lead to performance degradation.\\\\n2. Introducing `store::Iterable*` and `store::Unordered` comparison tests to demonstrate that the average performance is comparable and the edge-case performance is better.\\\\n\\\\n# Timeline and funding\\\\n\\\\nThe estimated timeline for delivery is within the next month, with a total funding requirement of 8000 USDT, paid once the PR is raised and ready for review.", "linked_proposals": [], "receiver_account": "22516c1b4e5d40db919e5e56a040c5670eac947fcb53a71207d5ce640a973820", "requested_sponsor": "neardevdao.near", "proposal_body_version": "V0", "requested_sponsorship_usd_amount": "8000", "requested_sponsorship_paid_in_currency": "USDT"}, "labels": []}
